        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 12:59PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 1259 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from over Fort Collins to near Pinewood
Springs, or extending from over Fort Collins to 27 miles southwest
of Fort Collins, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Collins, Loveland, Windsor, Berthoud, Lyons, Timnath,
Masonville, Carter Lake, Cedar Cove, Drake, Bellvue, Pinewood
Springs, Laporte, Campion and Horsetooth Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
